args: I sense great disquiet here.\nWhat trouble ails you, friends?
We got a tip that the Empire'd attacked a\nnearby village, so he headed out with a\nteam to deal with it.
But that was three days ago.\nIt's been too long. Somethin' ain't right.
Ezelith! You were part of the team that was\nwith {player_name}, right?
If YOU got thrashed, somethin' bad is\nafoot. Are the others who went with you\nokay? What happened?!
We played right into their hands.
The villagers were in on it. The Empire\nknew that if they spread word a village\nwas under attack, we'd come running.
It was an ambush. There were so many\nof them. They had us cornered...
{player_name} told me to come\nand get help. I barely made it out alive...
But the others... They're still...\n{player_name}'s still in danger!
Please. You have to...go and save him,\nyou...big lunk...
We will. Don't you worry about a thing.\nWe'll take it from here. You rest easy.
You heard the gal! We gotta hurry!
(This isn't good. They've split us in half,\nand everyone is exhausted, besides. At\nthis rate, we won't—)
If you do, I can't make any promises\nabout what happens to the girl.
Rgh... Why? Why are you...helping them?
You really gotta ask? We just have to hand\nyou over, and they'll make sure we never\ngo without again.
I'm never letting one bad harvest mean we\nhave to pick who lives and dies again!
Please, listen to me... Whatever they told\nyou, I can promise you that they'll never\ngive you the future you desire.
What you're doing is useless. There is too\nlarge a gap between your power and his.
Even in numbers, even if you take\nhostages, you have no hope of taking\n{player_name} captive.
Nrgh! Well... Well, then we'll at least\nmake an offering of your head!
(Cleo! Dammit, there's no way to save her\nwithout killing the villagers!)
Rrgh! Do I really have no choice?!
Foolish, pitiable denizens of this land...\nYour petty machinations are undone before\nme, as the dew fades in morning's sun.
If you would ask my identity, I shall oblige!\nFor I am the mad cyclone, protector of fate\nand friend alike—Grimnir, war-god!
Grimnir! You're a welcome sight!\nAre you unharmed, Cleo?!
I am fine. You have my thanks, Grimnir!
...NAILED IT! That was absolutely bang-on\nthat time! MAN, I am awesome!
Oh, er... *AHEM* Now, downtrodden\nmasses. Lay down your arms, or face the\nwar-god's judgment!
What's WITH this guy?! Rrgh, I'm not\nabout to surrender to some washed-up\ntheater kid!
Heh. Pitiable indeed. Then taste the wind\nof my whirlwin...wait, that's two winds.\nUhhh... UHHH...! HAVE AT YOU!
You truly saved us today, Grimnir. Had\nyou not come to our aid, I fear that—
...Yes. I fear I'd steeled my heart to do just\nthat.
I don't doubt it. In order to save his\nfellow, the seventh scion of Alberia did\nstrike down the villagers.
Though betrayed by those he was tasked to\nprotect and left no other choice, their end\ncast an indelible shadow upon his soul...
Is that...a premonition of my future self?
In another timeline, perhaps. But that is\nnot the future that awaits you, Prince.
Yet perhaps, as a steward of causality,\nit was not my place to intervene today.
Do you regret it, then? That your actions\ntoday changed the course of history?
It's nothing you need concern yourself\nwith. Each branch of time affects the rest.
The pain you were spared today will return\nto find you in some other way, upon some\nother day.
My actions here held little meaning,\nin the end.
